:"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"nosuid\" mount option causes the system not to execute \"setuid\" and \"setgid\" files with owner privileges. This option must be used for mounting any file system not containing approved \"setuid\" and \"setguid\" files. Executing files from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for nonprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6728","uuid":"ec2ad644-13ca-4593-af35-a1b66f985bce","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E490C6310E4AB5AB04540B3E54A78DBA5D7DD346\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 9 must prevent files with the setuid and setgid bit set from being executed on file systems that are used with removable media.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257860","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257860","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257860","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-257860r1044940_rule","rule_id":"SV-257860","rule_version":"RHEL-09-231095","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must mount /boot with the nodev option.","fix_text":"Modify \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nodev\" option on the \"/boot\" directory.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that the \"/boot\" mount point has the \"nodev\" option with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep '\\s/boot\\s'\n\n/dev/sda1 on /boot type xfs (rw,nodev,relatime,seclabel,attr2)\n\nIf the \"/boot\" file system does not have the \"nodev\" option set, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The only legitimate location for device files is the \"/dev\" directory located on the root partition. The only exception to this is chroot jails.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"3543","uuid":"b0940d5f-a90f-4cfd-a66b-f71da0dd11d1","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C6E5A11F3E825EBDDDAB4E830B971D01D33AAC3B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 9 must mount /boot with the nodev option.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257861","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257861","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257861","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-257861r1044941_rule","rule_id":"SV-257861","rule_version":"RHEL-09-231100","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must prevent files with the setuid and setgid bit set from being executed on the /boot directory.","fix_text":"Modify \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nosuid\" option on the \"/boot\" directory.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the /boot directory is mounted with the \"nosuid\" option with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep '\\s/boot\\s'\n\n/dev/sda1 on /boot type xfs (rw,nosuid,relatime,seclabe,attr2,inode64,noquota)\n\nIf the /boot file system does not have the \"nosuid\" option set, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"nosuid\" mount option causes the system not to execute \"setuid\" and \"setgid\" files with owner privileges. This option must be used for mounting any file system not containing approved \"setuid\" and \"setguid\" files. Executing files from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for nonprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"3959","uuid":"8ac4a016-1d9b-4598-91e2-3446990afd8d","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1100FFACEC75DA5F1E29D1CC560B9B68D985E79D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 9 must prevent files with the setuid and setgid bit set from being executed on the /boot directory.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257862","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257862","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257862","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-257862r1184295_rule","rule_id":"SV-257862","rule_version":"RHEL-09-231105","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must prevent files with the setuid and setgid bit set from being executed on the /boot/efi directory.","fix_text":"Modify \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nosuid\" option on the \"/boot/efi\" directory.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: For systems that use BIOS, this is not applicable. \n\nVerify the /boot/efi directory is mounted with the \"nosuid\" option with the following command:\n\n$ mount | grep '\\s/boot/efi\\s'\n\n/dev/sda1 on /boot/efi type vfat (rw,nosuid,relatime,fmask=0077,dmask=0077,codepage=437,iocharset=ascii,shortname=winnt,errors=remount-ro)\n\nIf the /boot/efi file system does not have the \"nosuid\" option set, this is a finding.\n\nNote: This control is not applicable to vfat file systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"nosuid\" mount option causes the system not to execute \"setuid\" and \"setgid\" files with owner privileges. This option must be used for mounting any file system not containing approved \"setuid\" and \"setguid\" files. Executing files from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for nonprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"3753","uuid":"10b295a8-f5ea-4b16-8474-d1776c3995a0","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 450D2ABDE81D7E1D6BA01412B1651A2D900F1B22\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 9 must prevent files with the setuid and setgid bit set from being executed on the /boot/efi directory.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257863","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257863","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257863","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-257863r1155633_rule","rule_id":"SV-257863","rule_version":"RHEL-09-231110","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must mount /dev/shm with the nodev option.","fix_text":"Configure \"/dev/shm\" to mount with the \"nodev\" option.\n\nModify \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nodev\" option on the \"/dev/shm\" file system.\n\nTo reload all implicit mount units and update the dependency graph so that new options will apply correctly at next remount, run the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl daemon-reload\n\nUse the following command to apply the changes immediately without a reboot:\n\n$ sudo mount -o remount /dev/shm","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify \"/dev/shm\" is mounted with the \"nodev\" option with the following command:\n\n$ findmnt /dev/shm\n\nTARGET   SOURCE FSTYPE OPTIONS\n/dev/shm tmpfs  tmpfs  rw,nodev,nosuid,noexec,seclabel\n\nIf the mount options for /dev/shm does not include nodev, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"nodev\" mount option causes the system to not interpret character or block special devices. Executing character or block special devices from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for nonprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.\n\nThe only legitimate location for device files is the \"/dev\" directory located on the root partition, with the exception of chroot jails if implemented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"4073","uuid":"0dec4aaf-8039-4647-914c-ff97d9aaa48a","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7058C68791C0FD7EA9C6E5B12AF1B8592FC63913\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'RHEL 9 must mount /dev/shm with the nodev option.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257864","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257864","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257864","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-257864r1155639_rule","rule_id":"SV-257864","rule_version":"RHEL-09-231115","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must mount /dev/shm with the noexec option.","fix_text":"Configure \"/dev/shm\" to mount with the \"noexec\" option.\n\nModify \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"noexec\" option on the \"/dev/shm\" file system.\n\nTo reload all implicit mount units and update the dependency graph so that new options will apply correctly at next remount, run the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl daemon-reload\n\nUse the following command to apply the changes immediately without a reboot:\n\n$ sudo mount -o remount /dev/shm","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify \"/dev/shm\" is mounted with the \"noexec\" option with the following command:\n\n$ findmnt /dev/shm\n\n/dev/shm tmpfs  tmpfs  rw,nodev,nosuid,noexec,seclabel\n\nIf the mount options for /dev/shm does not include noexec, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"noexec\" mount option causes the system to not execute binary files. This option must be used for mounting any file system not containing approved binary files, as they may be incompatible. Executing files from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for nonprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"3603","uuid":"14ff13a7-77c5-4186-9aa2-9049ec9a1cd7","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A4B2D0918532E375CA06F9FF69B0972EE31E1615\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 9 must mount /dev/shm with the noexec option.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257865","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257865","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257865","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-257865r1184297_rule","rule_id":"SV-257865","rule_version":"RHEL-09-231120","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must mount /dev/shm with the nosuid option.","fix_text":"Configure \"/dev/shm\" to mount with the \"nosuid\" option.\n\nModify \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nosuid\" option on the \"/dev/shm\" file system.\n\nTo reload all implicit mount units and update the dependency graph so that new options will apply correctly at next remount, run the following command:\n\n$ sudo systemctl daemon-reload\n\nUse the following command to apply the changes immediately without a reboot:\n\n$ sudo mount -o remount /dev/shm","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify \"/dev/shm\" is mounted with the \"nosuid\" option with the following command:\n\n$ findmnt /dev/shm\n/dev/shm tmpfs  tmpfs  rw,nodev,nosuid,noexec,seclabel\n\nIf the mount options for /dev/shm does not include nosuid, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"nosuid\" mount option causes the system to not execute \"setuid\" and \"setgid\" files with owner privileges. This option must be used for mounting any file system not containing approved \"setuid\" and \"setguid\" files. Executing files from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for nonprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"3278","uuid":"f1728fb1-db37-4a29-9e7a-b0ef7075342c","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A44F51BC63A884D076D5EC4B9A68659695D1FE9F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'RHEL 9 must mount /dev/shm with the nosuid option.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257866","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257866","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257866","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-257866r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-257866","rule_version":"RHEL-09-231125","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must mount /tmp with the nodev option.","fix_text":"Modify \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nodev\" option on the \"/tmp\" directory.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify \"/tmp\" is mounted with the \"nodev\" option:\n\n$ mount | grep /tmp\n\n/dev/mapper/rhel-tmp on /tmp type xfs (rw,nodev,nosuid,noexec,seclabel)\n\nIf the \"/tmp\" file system is mounted without the \"nodev\" option, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"nodev\" mount option causes the system to not interpret character or block special devices. Executing character or block special devices from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for nonprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.\n\nThe only legitimate location for device files is the \"