 of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.\n\nAudit records can be generated from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nWhen a user logs on, the auid is set to the uid of the account being authenticated. Daemons are not user sessions and have the loginuid set to -1. The auid representation is an unsigned 32-bit integer, which equals 4294967295. The audit system interprets -1, 4294967295, and \"unset\" in the same way.\n\nThe system call rules are loaded into a matching engine that intercepts each system call made by all programs on the system. Therefore, it is very important to use system call rules only when absolutely necessary since these affect performance. The more rules, the bigger the performance hit. The performance can be helped, however, by combining system calls into one rule whenever possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000172","CCI-002884"],"reference_identifier":"3878","uuid":"7c5565ea-29af-44e0-9172-4a7523522974","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 450065B3CEFA676F015B136669D829A6D1814D41\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'RHEL 9 must audit all uses of the su command.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-258204","group_tree":[{"id":"V-258204","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-258204","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-258204r1045397_rule","rule_id":"SV-258204","rule_version":"RHEL-09-654150","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must audit all uses of the sudo command.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 9 to generate audit records upon successful/unsuccessful attempts to use the \"sudo\" command by adding or updating the following rule in \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/bin/sudo -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k priv_cmd\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command:\n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that RHEL 9 is configured to audit the execution of the \"sudo\" command with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep '/usr/bin/sudo\\b'\n\n-a always,exit -S all -F path=/usr/bin/sudo -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=-1 -F key=priv_cmd\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit record specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.\n\nAudit records can be generated from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nWhen a user logs on, the auid is set to the uid of the account being authenticated. Daemons are not user sessions and have the loginuid set to -1. The auid representation is an unsigned 32-bit integer, which equals 4294967295. The audit system interprets -1, 4294967295, and \"unset\" in the same way.\n\nThe system call rules are loaded into a matching engine that intercepts each system call made by all programs on the system. Therefore, it is very important to use system call rules only when absolutely necessary since these affect performance. The more rules, the bigger the performance hit. The performance can be helped, however, by combining system calls into one rule whenever possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000172","CCI-002884"],"reference_identifier":"8865","uuid":"5aa10d06-485e-4919-b8de-2666ea7245ea","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-258205","group_tree":[{"id":"V-258205","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-258205","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-258205r1045400_rule","rule_id":"SV-258205","rule_version":"RHEL-09-654155","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must audit all uses of the sudoedit command.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 9 to generate audit records upon successful/unsuccessful attempts to use the \"sudoedit\" command by adding or updating the following rule in \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/bin/sudoedit -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k priv_cmd\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command:\n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that RHEL 9 is configured to audit the execution of the \"sudoedit\" command with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep /usr/bin/sudoedit\n\n-a always,exit -S all -F path=/usr/bin/sudoedit -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=-1 -F key=priv_cmd\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit record specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.\n\nAudit records can be generated from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nWhen a user logs on, the auid is set to the uid of the account being authenticated. Daemons are not user sessions and have the loginuid set to -1. The auid representation is an unsigned 32-bit integer, which equals 4294967295. The audit system interprets -1, 4294967295, and \"unset\" in the same way.\n\nThe system call rules are loaded into a matching engine that intercepts each system call made by all programs on the system. Therefore, it is very important to use system call rules only when absolutely necessary since these affect performance. The more rules, the bigger the performance hit. The performance can be helped, however, by combining system calls into one rule whenever possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000172","CCI-002884"],"reference_identifier":"1079","uuid":"083dbb47-3749-413a-ba47-bcbf5ded6e22","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B32906199A0A4D7C634A257975A6177F51043D2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'RHEL 9 must audit all uses of the sudoedit command.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-258206","group_tree":[{"id":"V-258206","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-258206","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-258206r1045403_rule","rule_id":"SV-258206","rule_version":"RHEL-09-654160","rule_title":"RHEL 9 must audit all uses of the unix_chkpwd command.","fix_text":"Configure RHEL 9 to generate audit records upon successful/unsuccessful attempts to use the \"unix_chkpwd\" command by adding or updating the following rule in \"/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules\":\n\n-a always,exit -F path=/usr/sbin/unix_chkpwd -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=unset -k privileged-unix-update\n\nTo load the rules to the kernel immediately, use the following command:\n\n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that RHEL 9 is configured to audit the execution of the \"unix_chkpwd\" command with the following command:\n\n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep unix_chkpwd\n\n-a always,exit -S all -F path=/usr/sbin/unix_chkpwd -F perm=x -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=-1 -F key=privileged-unix-update\n\nIf the command does not return a line, or the line is commented out, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_9_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit record specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one.\n\nAudit records can be generated from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nWhen a user logs on, the auid is set to the uid of the account being authenticated. Daemons are not user sessions and have the loginuid set to -1. The auid representation is an unsigned 32-bit integer, which equals 4294967295. The audit system interprets -1, 4294967295, and \"unset\" in the same way.\n\nThe system call rules are loaded into a matching engine that intercepts each system call made by all programs on the system. Therefore, it is very important to use system call rules only when absolutely necessary since these affect performance. The more rules, the bigger the performance hit. The performance can be helped, however, by combining system calls into one rule whenever possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000172","CCI-002884"],"reference_identifier":"3317","uuid":"0dae7275-0dcb-401c-968c-9567616f7147","stig_uuid":"6cc2160c-e4e9-459c-970b-2f2c250586dd","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F895C62DCFBD23DF34634B2380BDAAA4B54E2FA7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'RHEL 9 must audit all uses of the unix_chkpwd command.' matches the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-258207","group_tree":[{"id":"V-258207","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-258207","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","rule_id_src":"SV-258207r